   HONGKONG-GURKHAS (Hong Kong) _ When tycoons step out of their
Rolls-Royces here these days, they are often quickly surrounded by
a phalanx of compact but fierce-looking bodyguards. These are
Gurkhas, and while they come from the uplands of Nepal, they are
deeply embedded in Hong Kong's history. By Mark Landler.
</P>
