<P>
   SCI-BRAIN-CELLS (Undated) _ It has long been thought that,
unlike other cells of the body, brain cells are not replaced when
they die, but a research team has proven for the first time that
human brain cells can regenerate. By Holcomb B. Noble.
</P>
