<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    U.S. OIL RESERVES: SAVING FOR A RAINY DAY . . . OR AN EMBARGO
 &HT;    With OIL-FUTURE-$ADV01.
 &HT;    Moving in both the (w) Washington and (k) Commentary categories.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., Nov. 1 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By ANDREW MOLLISON 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   STRATEGIC PETROLEUM RESERVE
</P>
<P>
   The Strategic Petroleum Reserve is an emergency supply of crude
oil stored by the federal government in huge underground salt
caverns along the Texas and Louisiana gulf coastline.
</P>
<P>
   STORAGE
SITE........................CAPACITY........................AMOUNT
STORED
</P>
<P>
   Bryan Mound, Texas ... 226 million barrels ...... 217 million
barrels
</P>
<P>
   Big Hill, Texas ............. 160 million barrels ........ 81
million barrels
</P>
<P>
   West Hackberry, La. ... 219 million barrels ..... 193 million
barrels
</P>
<P>
   Bayou Choctaw, La. ....... 75 million barrels ........ 66
million barrels
</P>
<P>
   Weeks Island, La. ........... 72 million barrels ........... 1
million barrels (a)
</P>
<P>
   TOTAL .............................. 752 million barrels ......
558 million barrels
</P>
<P>
   (a) Weeks Island leaked, and is being decommissioned.
</P>
<P>
   Source: U.S. Department of Energy.
</P>
<P>
   PERCENTAGE OF ENERGY FROM PETROLEUM
</P>
<P>
   Average in U.S. ... 38.3 percent
</P>
<P>
   Florida ................... 50.2 percent
</P>
<P>
   Colorado ................ 37.1 percent
</P>
<P>
   Georgia .................. 37.6 percent
</P>
<P>
   Ohio ......................... 31.5 percent
</P>
<P>
   North Carolina .... 38.6 percent
</P>
<P>
   Texas ...................... 45.2 percent
</P>
<P>
   Source: U.S. Department of Energy. Latest (1995) data.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
