<P>
   BOOMERS-SPACE (Undated) _ Space age nostalgia runs deep among
baby boomers. For us, the space program of old promised not only
real-life outer-space adventures but also the hope of a brave new
world back home _ flying cars, plastic houses, Tang. By Frank
DeCaro. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PEA-COAT-FASHION (Undated) _ Despite the peacoat's universal
appeal, it has been hard in recent years to find one at anywhere
other than an Army-Navy surplus store. This year, a variety of
designer versions have dropped anchor. Polo Ralph Lauren on Madison
Avenue has an archetypal peacoat, in rigid wool, roomy enough for a
brawny deckhand and with an anchor etched onto each plastic button,
for $297.50. By David Colman. &QL; 
 &QL;
