<P>
   GAFANS _ JACKSONVILLE _ For many years, the Georgia-Florida
series was one of the most anticipated matchups in college
football. Fans would leave Athens as early as a week before the
game and most would leave by Thursday traveling to Jacksonville.
The series lost a little luster earlier this decade for two reasons
- renovation of the former Gator Bowl Stadium forced the games to
be played on campus for two years and Florida began to dominate by
winning seven straight games. After last year's 37-17 victory by
Georgia, Bulldog fans are excited once again on the heels on
today's game. (Brice, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
