DIGITAL-LA (Los Angeles) _ The Internet and related communications
technologies won't necessarily shrink the global village or have a
``Big Mac'' effect on culture, according to speakers at the Getty
Center's recent ``Communicating Culture'' conference. By David
Bloom.
