<P>
   GLENN-MISSION (Houston) _ Astronaut John Glenn begins geriatric
tests on his first full day in orbit while his fellow crew members
on the shuttle Discovery release a naval communications satellite.
And the crew gets a glimpse of Perth, Australia, where residents
turned on lights as they did during Glenn's first space mission 36
years ago. By MARK CARREAU.
