<P>
   US-ECONOMY (Washington) _ The nation's economy steamed ahead in
the third quarter, defying expectations the economic crisis in Asia
and Latin America would prompt a more dramatic slowdown here. The
U.S. gross domestic product _ the sum of all goods and service
produced in the country _ grew at a robust 3.3 percent for the
three months ending Sept. 30, the U.S. Commerce Department reports.
By DAVID IVANOVICH. (Already filed.)
