<HEADLINE>
BUDROYALE FAVORED IN CAL CUP CLASSIC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA _ Budroyale is the new, 8-5 favorite for the $250,000
California Cup Classic, highlight of the 10-race card today that
showcases the state's breeding industry.
</P>
<P>
   Cavonnier was the 9-5 favorite on the morning line before being
scratched Thursday because of a hind-leg injury, delaying the 1996
Santa Anita Derby winner's comeback from a nearly 2{-year layoff. A
field of six remains.
</P>
<P>
   Budroyale, a 5-year-old gelding ridden by Garrett Gomez, has won
7 of 12 starts at Santa Anita. Trainer Ted West hopes the son of
Cee's Tizzy will get the lead early in the 1[-mile race.
</P>
<P>
   ``It appears he has a chance to go 46 (seconds) and change on
the lead, and that will definitely help him,'' West said.
</P>
<P>
   Budroyale, whose biggest victory came in the San Bernardino
Handicap in April, finished second in the Pomona Handicap at
Fairplex Park last time out as winner Score Quick got loose on the
lead.
</P>
<P>
   Pacificbounty (Eddie Delahoussaye riding) is second on the
Classic morning line at 5-2, followed by 3-1 Bagshot (Alex Solis),
9-2 Kingdom Found (Kent Desormeaux), 8-1 Mateo (David Flores) and
20-1 Funny Tale (Gary Stevens).
</P>
<P>
   The Cal Cup is a nine-year-old event that features a Breeders'
Cup-style array of races for both genders and all specialties but
is restricted to Cal-bred horses. The purses total $1.2 million.
First post is at noon.
</P>
<P>
   Large, competitive fields are the rule, though there are two
deservedly heavy favorites today, 4-5 Magical Allure (unbeaten in
six starts) in the Matron and 7-5 Controlled (unbeaten in three
starts) in the Juvenile Fillies.
</P>
<P>
   Pick-six players will chase a pool guaranteed by the Oak Tree
Racing Association to total at least $2 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
