QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-POLITICS-HACKERS-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``If you have 10 people at a protest, they don't do much of
anything. If you have 10 people on line, they could cripple a
network.''
</P>
<P>
   _OXBLOOD RUFFIAN, a pseudonym for a Toronto-based computer
fanatic.
</P>
